cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.AI, cs.CR, cs.SY

The paper discusses technologies related to wireless communications systems, specifically focusing on spectrum sensing and adaptive spectrum hyperspace access. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also discusses signal identification and interference avoidance, which are topics related to information theory, making cs.IT (Information Theory) another likely category. The paper also mentions the need for intelligent and aware wireless communications systems, which suggests the possibility of using artificial intelligence techniques, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) a likely category as well. The paper also discusses cognitive radio systems, which fall under the category of cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). Finally, the paper discusses the need for autonomous adaptation of sensing parameters, which suggests the possibility of using control theory techniques, making cs.SY (Systems and Control) a possible category as well.
